  isbn = {979-8-3315-3447-9},
  publisher = {IEEE},
  abstract = {Paper is the type of cultural relic most readily affected by temperature, humidity and light, and it is therefore liable to irreversible physical and chemical damage; an intelligent environmental monitoring and control system for paper-relic conservation is designed and developed that uses a range of sensors to monitor temperature, relative humidity, illuminance and micro-pressure differentials, stores these parameters on a computer and regulates micro-environmental humidity and illuminance so as to protect paper relics more effectively; experiments show that the system provides reliable parameter measurement and regulation for the preservation of paper cultural relics. Paper cultural relics protection intelligent environment control system with STM32H562VGT6 as the microcontroller, humidity control has the characteristics of nonlinearity, time-varying, time-lagging and susceptible to external interference, conventional PID is difficult to apply. A fuzzy PID control algorithm combining fuzzy control and conventional PID is used. The algorithm takes the error between the current value of the relative humidity at the air outlet of the system and the target value, the rate of change of the error as the input, and the amount of change of the P, I, D parameters as the output, and realizes the real-time parameter adjustment of the PID control. After simulation analysis, the algorithm is better than conventional PID in terms of micro-overshooting amount, response speed and anti-interference. The measured results show that the algorithm is lower than the conventional PID control algorithm in overshooting amount under multiple humidity control target values, and the response speed is faster; it is characterized by a small overshooting amount, fast response speed and robustness, and it is suitable for humidity control of the protection of paper artifacts.},
