  year = {2025},
  pages = {153--159},
  doi = {10.1109/ICNC-FSKD67701.2025.11198072},
  isbn = {979-8-3315-7535-9},
  publisher = {IEEE},
  abstract = {Blockchain technology has been widely applied in fields such as finance, supply chain, healthcare, and real estate. Aviation fuel is the largest operating cost item for airlines, accounting for 30\\\%-40\\\% of China Southern Airlines' operating costs, with an annual expenditure exceeding 30 billion CNY. However, the traditional aviation fuel settlement model suffers from systemic pain points due to paper document circulation, manual reconciliation, and multi-level approval processes, including lengthy procedures (single settlement takes 72 hours), significant capital tie-up (average accounts payable turnover of 45 days annually), and high dispute resolution costs (1.2 \% reconciliation error rate). These issues simultaneously lead to prolonged payment cycles for aviation fuel suppliers, lack of high-quality supply chain scenarios for financial institutions, and limited bargaining power for airlines, creating tripartite conflicts. Aiming at the intelligent settlement of aviation fuel for China Southern Airlines, in this paper, we firstly establish a digital aviation fuel settlement platform, which integrates blockchain, smart contracts, and Robotic Process Automation (RPA) technologies through three-dimensional collaborative innovation across technology, process, and finance. Then, we propose a novel real-time settlement model based on blockchain smart contracts, achieving systematic restructuring of the settlement patterns within the aviation fuel supply chain. The research demonstrates that blockchain smart contract technology, by reconstructing the settlement trust mechanism and value distribution rules, can provide a reusable technical paradigm and business logic for the digital transformation of the aviation energy supply chain, and holds significant practical value for improving overall supply chain operational efficiency.},
